KeyFromEnv(), AuthMiddleware() (JWT RS256 verification) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go` | 20 | Config struct (Port, Workspace), ParseFlags() CLI parser |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go` | 51 | Constants (TimeoutExitCode=124, MaxBodySize=32MiB, PublicKeyEnvVar), request/response structs |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute.go` | 108 | ExecuteHandler -- command execution with timeout, working dir, env vars |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go` | 339 | Legacy file handlers (UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler, sanitizePath, parseFileMode) |\n\n#### 2.2 picod/files/ subpackage\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/types.go` | 204 | FileManager interface (12 methods), all request/response structs, constants, sentinel errors |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/manager.go` | 46 | NewFileManager() constructor with config defaults and temp dir creation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/sanitize.go` | 73 | sanitizePath() method (workspace jail), parseFileMode(), parseOctal() |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/read.go` | 63 | ReadFile() -- offset/limit reading, Base64 encoding |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/write.go` | 70 | WriteFile() -- overwrite/append/at-offset modes, Base64 decoding |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/stat.go` | 32 | StatFile() -- metadata via os.Lstat, symlink detection |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/list.go` | 50 | ListFiles() -- directory listing |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/upload.go` | 174 | UploadFile() + UploadFileChunked() + mergeChunks() + cleanupChunks() |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/download.go` | 131 | DownloadFile() + handleRangeRequest() + parseRange() (HTTP Range support) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/delete.go` | 52 | DeleteFile() -- single and batch deletion with partial failure reporting |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/move.go` | 40 | MoveFile() -- os.Rename with dual path sanitization |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/mkdir.go` | 32 | MkDir() -- recursive directory creation with custom mode |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/search.go` | 72 | SearchFiles() -- glob pattern search with depth limit |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/chmod.go` | 39 | Chmod() -- permission changes with octal mode parsing |\n\n#### 2.3 picod test files\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth_test.go` | 247 | AuthManager + AuthMiddleware tests (key loading, valid/expired/malformed tokens, HS256 rejection, MaxBodySize) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server_test.go` | 102 | Server initialization, route registration, health endpoint public, API requires auth |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config_test.go` | 54 | ParseFlags defaults, custom values, workspace resolution |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute_test.go` | 255 | ExecuteHandler tests (valid execution, timeout, empty command, malformed JSON, working dir, env vars) + authedRequest() helper |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/health_test.go` | 74 | HealthCheckHandler response, uptime, no-auth-required |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/sanitize_test.go` | 121 | sanitizePath tests (normal path, traversal blocked, absolute path stripped, symlink escape blocked, empty workspace) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/manager_test.go` | 68 | NewFileManager defaults, custom config, invalid workspace, temp dir creation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/sanitize_test.go` | 108 | sanitizePath tests in files/ subpackage |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/read_test.go` | 146 | ReadFile tests (entire file, offset, offset+limit, exceeds size, negative offset, directory, not found, traversal) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/write_test.go` | 140 | WriteFile tests (overwrite, append, at-offset, create-parent, no-create-parent, invalid base64, to-directory) |\n\n---\n\n### 3. EXISTING MIDDLEWARE PATTERNS\n\n#### 3.1 PicoD AuthMiddleware (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Loads RSA public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable at startup\n- Uses RS256 (RSA + SHA-256) for JWT verification\n- Requires `exp` and `iat` claims with 1-minute leeway\n- Rejects non-RSA signing methods explicitly\n- On success: wraps request body with `http.MaxBytesReader` (32 MiB limit)\n- On failure: returns 401 with `{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"...\"}`\n- Applied to `/api` route group only; `/health` is public\n- Fatal exit on startup if public key cannot be loaded\n\n#### 3.2 Router AuthMiddleware (`pkg/router/middleware.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        // Extract Authorization header\n        // Validate Bearer format\n        // Call jwtManager.ParseAndValidateToken(token)\n        // On success: c.Set(\"claims\", claims) + c.Next()\n        // On failure: 401 with error code\n    }\n}\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses `JWTManager.ParseAndValidateToken()` for validation\n- Stores parsed claims in Gin context via `c.Set(\"claims\", claims)`\n- Differentiated error codes: `UNAUTHORIZED`, `TOKEN_EXPIRED`\n- Applied to `/v1` route group\n- Middleware order: `gin.Logger()` -> `gin.Recovery()` -> `AuthMiddleware()` -> `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware()`\n\n#### 3.3 Router Additional Middleware (`pkg/router/middleware.go`)\n\n- **ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware**: Semaphore-based rate limiting (returns 429 when overloaded)\n- **RequestLoggerMiddleware**: Logs method, path, status, duration_ms, trace_id\n- **TraceIDMiddleware**: Generates UUID trace ID per request\n\n---\n\n### 4. TASKS.MD FORMAT\n\nFound 17 tasks.md files in `changes/AR-001/` through `changes/AR-017/`.\n\n**Format pattern (from AR-017):**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX -- Title -- Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/xxx\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** S|M|L\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-XXX/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-XXX/design.md`\n\n## T1. TODO\n\n- [ ] 1.1 TODO\n\n**Verification:** TODO\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | ... | `go build ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC2 | ... | `go test ./pkg/xxx/... -v -count=1` |\n| AC3 | ... | `go test -race ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC4 | ... | `go vet ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n```\n\n**More detailed example (AR-016, 515 lines):** Has 19 tasks (T1-T19) with detailed sub-tasks, verification criteria, dependency graph (ASCII art), parallel execution notes, and 24 acceptance criteria.\n\n---\n\n### 5. DESIGN DOCUMENTS FOR ST-3 AND AR-017\n\n**ST-3** is referenced as \"Stage ST-3 (Design Complete)\" -- it is a precondition stage, not a separate design document. All AR tasks reference it as a completed prerequisite.\n\n**AR-017 documents:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md` (269 lines) -- Purpose, scope, architecture, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/design.md` (462 lines) -- Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, deployment, implementation steps (4 phases, all marked [x])\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md` (303 lines) -- Gherkin-style requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md` (32 lines) -- Minimal task file with placeholder T1\n\n**AR-016 documents (related, for context):**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/design.md` -- NOT present (uses root-level `design.md`)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` (1563 lines) -- Comprehensive design for PicoD File Management API\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` (870 lines) -- Delta spec for AR-016\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md` (515 lines) -- 19 tasks with detailed sub-tasks and dependency graph\n\n---\n\n### 6. GO.MOD -- DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go version:** 1.25.0\n\n**Direct dependencies:**\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT RS256 signing/verification |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation (trace IDs) |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.73 | Valkey client |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | v2.37.0 | Redis mock for testing |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes apimachinery |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Controller runtime |\n| `golang.org/x/net` | v0.51.0 | HTTP/2, h2c support |\n\n---\n\n### 7. JWT-RELATED CODE AND CONFIGURATION\n\n#### 7.1 PicoD JWT (pkg/picod/auth.go)\n- **Constants:** `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20`\n- **Key loading:** PEM-decoded PKIX RSA public key from environment variable\n- **Validation:** `jwt.Parse()` with `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n- **Signing method check:** Explicit `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA` type assertion in KeyFunc\n\n#### 7.2 Router JWT (pkg/router/jwt.go)\n- **JWTManager struct:** Holds `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`, `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`, `clientset kubernetes.Interface`, `config *JWTConfig`\n- **Key generation:** 2048-bit RSA key pair via `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)`\n- **Key persistence:** K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default: \"default\")\n- **Token generation:** `GenerateToken(claims)` -- RS256, exp from config (default 5min), iat = now, iss = \"agentcube-router\"\n- **Token validation:** `ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString)` -- RS256 verify, leeway from config (default 1min), issuer check\n- **Error semantics:** \"invalid signature\", \"token is expired\", \"invalid issuer\", \"invalid token\", \"unexpected signing method\"\n\n#### 7.3 Router JWT Config (pkg/router/config.go)\n```go\ntype JWTConfig struct {\n    Expiration time.Duration  // default: 5 * time.Minute\n    Issuer     string         // default: \"agentcube-router\"\n    Leeway     time.Duration  // default: 1 * time.Minute\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. AUTHENTICATION/AUTHORIZATION CURRENT STATE\n\n#### 8.1 PicoD (sandbox daemon)\n- **Authentication:** JWT RS256 via `AuthMiddleware` on all `/api/*` routes\n- **Key distribution:** RSA public key injected via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable by WorkloadManager from K8s Secret\n- **Authorization:** None (authentication only -- no RBAC, no role-based access)\n- **Public endpoints:** `/health` only (for K8s liveness/readiness probes)\n- **Startup behavior:** Fatal exit if public key cannot be loaded (fail-secure)\n\n#### 8.2 Router (gateway)\n- **Authentication:** JWT RS256 via `AuthMiddleware` on all `/v1/*` routes\n- **Key management:** RSA key pair generated at startup, persisted to K8s Secret `picod-router-identity`\n- **Outbound signing:** Router signs new JWTs when forwarding requests to sandbox/PicoD\n- **Authorization:** None (authentication only)\n- **Public endpoints:** `/health/live`, `/health/ready`\n- **Additional protection:** ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware (429 on overload)\n\n#### 8.3 Auth flow\n```\nClient --> Router (validates client JWT via RS256)\n         --> Router signs new JWT (RS256, 5min expiry)\n         --> PicoD (validates Router JWT via RS256 public key)\n              --> Valid: execute command / file operation\n              --> Invalid: 401\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. EXISTING TEST PATTERNS\n\n#### 9.1 Testing framework\n- **Library:** `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert, require)\n- **HTTP testing:** `net/http/httptest` (NewRequest, NewRecorder)\n- **Gin mode:** `gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)` for test isolation\n- **Temp directories:** `t.TempDir()` for isolated test workspaces\n- **Helper pattern:** `t.Helper()` on test helper functions\n\n#### 9.2 Common test patterns\n\n**Auth helper (picod):**\n```go\nfunc authedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body []byte) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\n```\n- Generates test RSA key pair, sets public key on server's authManager\n- Signs JWT with RS256, adds `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Uses `httptest.ResponseRecorder` for response capture\n\n**Key generation helpers (picod):**\n```go\nfunc generateTestPrivateKey(t *testing.T) *rsa.PrivateKey\nfunc generateTestPublicKey(t *testing.T) string\nfunc signTestToken(t *testing.T, key *rsa.PrivateKey, claims jwt.MapClaims) string\n```\n\n**Environment variable cleanup:**\n```go\nos.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, pubKey)\ndefer os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n```\n\n**Table-driven tests:** Not heavily used; most tests are individual functions with descriptive names.\n\n**Error assertion:** Uses `require.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrXxx)` for sentinel errors, `assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"substring\")` for error messages.\n\n**Test naming convention:** `Test{Component}_{Scenario}` (e.g., `TestReadFile_EntireFile`, `TestAuthMiddleware_ExpiredToken`, `TestSanitizePath_ParentTraversal`)\n\n#### 9.3 Test coverage by component\n\n| Component | Test file | Key test scenarios |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------------|\n| AuthManager | auth_test.go | Valid key load, missing env, invalid PEM, NonRSA key (note: NonRSA test actually passes because it generates RSA key) |\n| AuthMiddleware | auth_test.go | Missing header, malformed header, valid token, expired token, non-RSA signing (HS256), MaxBodySize wrapping |\n| Server | server_test.go | Field initialization, timestamp, health public, API requires auth, all routes registered |\n| Execute | execute_test.go | Valid execution, custom timeout, timeout exceeded, invalid timeout, empty command, malformed JSON, non-zero exit, working dir, invalid working dir, env augmentation |\n| Health | health_test.go | Response fields, uptime increases, no auth required |\n| SanitizePath (picod) | sanitize_test.go | Simple relative, traversal blocked, absolute stripped, symlink allowed, symlink escape blocked, empty workspace, workspace with symlinks, dotdot alone, dotdot+separator |\n| FileManager | files/manager_test.go | Defaults, custom config, invalid workspace, workspace resolution, temp dir creation |\n| SanitizePath (files) | files/sanitize_test.go | Normal path, subdirectory, absolute path, parent traversal, symlink escape, empty path, uninitialized workspace, symlink inside workspace, dotdot alone, dotdot+separator |\n| ReadFile | files/read_test.go | Entire file, with offset, with offset+limit, offset exceeds size, limit exceeds remaining, negative offset, directory, not found, path traversal |\n| WriteFile | files/write_test.go | Overwrite, append, at-offset, create-parent, no-create-parent, invalid base64, to-directory |\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY ARCHITECTURAL NOTES\n\n1. **Two JWT systems exist:** The Router's JWTManager (signs + validates) and PicoD's AuthManager (validates only). They share the same key pair distributed via K8s Secret.\n\n2. **Workspace jail:** Both `pkg/picod/files.go` and `pkg/picod/files/sanitize.go` have duplicate `sanitizePath` implementations. The files/ subpackage version is the newer, cleaner one.\n\n3. **Legacy files.go still exists:** The `pkg/picod/files.go` (339 lines) contains the old monolithic file handlers that AR-016 was supposed to replace with the `files/` subpackage. The `files/` subpackage has the FileManager interface and implementations but the Server still uses the old handlers from `files.go`.\n\n4. **AR-017 is marked complete in design.md:** All implementation phases are checked off `[x]` in the design document, and the code exists (auth.go, auth_test.go, server.go modifications). However, the tasks.md is a placeholder with only `T1. TODO`.\n\n5. **The NonRSAKey test has a bug:** In `auth_test.go`, `TestAuthManager_LoadPublicKeyFromEnv_NonRSAKey` generates an RSA key (not EC), so it actually tests the happy path, not the error path.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2876d7fb1ffeHKE0Y81ctCQWaY","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775844360267,"end":1775844615378}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775844615440,"sessionID":"ses_2876da30fffem0jOE59UJnZgLJ","part":{"id":"prt_d789664d500174M0DpUcqLDX4K","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78925de50013US10yiRsSKFtc","sessionID":"ses_2876da30fffem0jOE59UJnZgLJ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":15718,"input":15457,"output":228,"reasoning":33,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.004697043}}
